I really like this, and not just because of the format screw


18 Feb 2018 23:51






The format screw serves the narrative well, but the article works well with or without it. Why?

Because, honestly, is this SCP wrong? Even if it's a cognitohazard, it's not wrong about the SCP universe being in constant danger, and this place being a really nice place to ride out the storm (no pun intended).

I might personally not like the lack of technology, but if I were suddenly transplanted to the SCP reality I'd probably want to go here. Desire is rarely an emotion an SCP invokes in me, so +1 for that.





